title: New phenanthrenequinones from Cymbidium ensifolium roots and their anti-inflammatory activity on lipopolysaccharide-activated BV2 microglial cells
content:
RSC Adv., 2024, 14,28390-28400
DOI: 10.1039/D4RA04761C, Paper

May Thazin Thant, Hasriadi Hasriadi, Preeyaporn Poldorn, Siriporn Jungsuttiwong, Pornchai Rojsitthisak, Chotima Böttcher, Pasarapa Towiwat, Boonchoo Sritularak
The roots of Cymbidium ensifolium yielded a total of 17 compounds, comprising two new compounds (1–2), one new natural product (3), and 14 known compounds (4–17).
